Thanks Stefan.  I&#39;m definitely going to give this the old college try.  If I
get anything worthy I&#39;ll post.

k



  _____  

From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of
Stefan Bion
Sent: Wednesday, March 26, 2008 6:25 PM
To: Kristin Morris
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] Re: EVP maker



Hi Kristin,

start EVPmaker, and open the WAV file in it. You can do this by using
the Open button, or simply by &quot;drag&#39;n&#39;drop&quot; the file into EVPmaker. Next
check &quot;Use Cue List&quot;, and click on the button with the yellow arrow to
start playback. You can record the sound as usual to any
cassette/digital recorder or even into a recording software on the same
computer.

In my short test last night, I used the &quot;EVP Session&quot; function, which
however didn&#39;t record my own voice - but it was the easiest way to test
it. Using &quot;EVP Session&quot; is a bit complicated to explain, but it&#39;s all
written in the manual... ;-)

Hope this helps...

Stefan

-- 

&gt; Steve or Stefan - can one you email me as well. I downloaded the EVPM and
I
&gt; saved the speakjet tones to a wav file. Now what????

&gt; Any help for the feebly inept technological wannabe that is me would be
&gt; great! :-)

&gt; Thanks,

&gt; Kristin

&gt; _____ 

&gt; From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups &lt;mailto:EVP-ITC%40yahoogroups.com&gt; .com
[mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups &lt;mailto:EVP-ITC%40yahoogroups.com&gt; .com] On
Behalf Of
&gt; Stefan Bion
&gt; Sent: Wednesday, March 26, 2008 3:44 PM
&gt; To: Steve Hultay
&gt; Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] Re: EVP maker

&gt; Thanks, Steve. I didn&#39;t know that.




